00:51:02,477 --> 00:51:05,310
I kept a few souvenirs
from my former life.

690
00:51:05,355 --> 00:51:08,268
Ah, the heady days of space piracy.

691
00:51:09,276 --> 00:51:13,645
But even an Infinite lmprobability Drive

692
00:51:13,739 --> 00:51:16,026
requires coordinates.

693
00:51:16,158 --> 00:51:18,570
Which I happen to have.

694
00:51:18,660 --> 00:51:20,276
No, no, no.

695
00:51:20,412 --> 00:51:22,824
You don't get something
for nothing, Zaphod.

696
00:51:22,914 --> 00:51:25,531
You must bring me something in return.

697
00:51:25,667 --> 00:51:28,534
- What?
- A gun.

698
00:51:28,628 --> 00:51:30,619
- A gun?
- A very special gun,

699
00:51:30,672 --> 00:51:34,006
designed by the greatest computer
ever invented.

700
00:51:34,050 --> 00:51:37,008
But the only way to find it
is to go to Magrathea.

701
00:51:37,137 --> 00:51:41,597
Fine. I'll get your gun.
Just give me the coordinates.

702
00:51:41,683 --> 00:51:44,471
And what will you give me
to ensure your return?

703
00:51:45,353 --> 00:51:47,685
My word as president.

704
00:51:49,024 --> 00:51:52,517
No. I need a hostage.

705
00:51:55,030 --> 00:51:56,862
Only...

706
00:51:56,907 --> 00:52:02,198
...what does
Zaphod Beeblebrox treasure?

707
00:52:06,041 --> 00:52:08,032
Come on.

708
00:52:11,046 --> 00:52:12,878
Oh, no.

709
00:52:13,006 --> 00:52:15,794
Hey, take it easy now. Think about this.

710
00:52:15,884 --> 00:52:19,047
No, stop it.
That kind of tickles.

711
00:52:19,137 --> 00:52:22,721
Two heads are better than one.
Double your pleasure.

712
00:52:23,225 --> 00:52:26,559
It's not fair. You need me.

713
00:52:26,686 --> 00:52:30,896
Come back. Come back!
Don't leave me alone.

714
00:52:34,569 --> 00:52:35,980
Come back.

715
00:52:36,071 --> 00:52:39,905
And I thought I was the only one
who considered your boyfriend

716
00:52:39,950 --> 00:52:42,658
a narcissistic moron,
but the whole galaxy does.

717
00:52:42,744 --> 00:52:45,577
What about you?
"Excuse me, Mr Humma, sir."

718
00:52:45,622 --> 00:52:50,082
"We're not with him. We just came
to worship you." Very brave.

719
00:52:50,168 --> 00:52:52,159
Where the hell is Ford?

720
00:52:56,132 --> 00:52:57,384
By the left, march.

721
00:52:57,425 --> 00:53:02,670
Left, right, left, right, left, right.

722
00:53:02,764 --> 00:53:06,974
Mr President,
we're here for your protection.

723
00:53:07,477 --> 00:53:10,094
Fire upon the kidnapper.

724
00:53:10,814 --> 00:53:12,225
<i>Hey, come on.</i>

725
00:53:12,274 --> 00:53:14,891
The president is the kidnapper.
You'll kill him.

726
00:53:16,945 --> 00:53:18,936
It's locked.

727
00:53:21,825 --> 00:53:24,192
Thank you, darling. I'll be in touch.

728
00:53:29,457 --> 00:53:31,949
Come on, Zaphod, man.

729
00:53:35,463 --> 00:53:38,251
- Hey, what did I miss?
- What have you been doing?

730
00:53:38,300 --> 00:53:41,793
Field research. So they found
where we are? Belgium bummer.

731
00:53:41,887 --> 00:53:44,629
They're shooting at us.
What are we going to do?

732
00:53:44,764 --> 00:53:48,052
- I have an idea.
- Pushing him out and running away?

733
00:53:48,143 --> 00:53:50,601
What? He's the one they want.

734
00:53:50,645 --> 00:53:52,977
You can't go out there.
What are you doing?

735
00:53:54,232 --> 00:53:57,190
- Back off.
- What's going on?

736
00:53:58,862 --> 00:54:02,150
I have the president
and I will kill him, I swear.

737
00:54:02,240 --> 00:54:06,199
- Could that actually kill him?
- I don't think so.

738
00:54:06,328 --> 00:54:08,490
It's an aerosol can.

739
00:54:08,538 --> 00:54:11,075
OK, frightened now, frightened.

740
00:54:12,709 --> 00:54:16,168
- Hi, little guy.
- Get her.

741
00:54:16,254 --> 00:54:19,246
- Zaphod, no, come on.
- Arthur.

742
00:54:20,050 --> 00:54:22,883
- Arthur.
- Tricia.

743
00:54:22,969 --> 00:54:25,961
- Arthur.
- Tricia. Wait.

744
00:54:34,898 --> 00:54:37,435
Arthur.

745
00:54:40,195 --> 00:54:43,187
Resistance is useless.

746
00:54:53,166 --> 00:54:56,909
<i>Bring her to Vogsphere
for processing, captain.</i>

747
00:54:58,672 --> 00:55:00,413
Circus. Circus!

748
00:55:00,507 --> 00:55:03,169
They got her and it's my fault.
We have to go.

749
00:55:03,218 --> 00:55:04,708
Let's go.

750
00:55:08,306 --> 00:55:10,343
Computer, take us to Magrathea.

751
00:55:10,392 --> 00:55:12,884
What? No.
We've got to go after Tricia.

752
00:55:12,936 --> 00:55:14,392
- Who?
- Trillian.

753
00:55:14,437 --> 00:55:17,975
They've got Trillian,
you stupid half-brained git.

754
00:55:18,066 --> 00:55:20,398
Right, you're coming out.

755
00:55:21,236 --> 00:55:25,195
Computer, we don't want to go to
Magrathea, we want to follow the ships.

756
00:55:25,240 --> 00:55:28,904
<i>I'd love to, but my guidance system
has been deactivated.</i>

757
00:55:29,035 --> 00:55:30,116
Oh, come on.

758
00:55:30,245 --> 00:55:32,612
<i>I'm sorry. It wasn't my fault.</i>

759
00:55:32,747 --> 00:55:34,738
What you doing on this ship?

760
00:55:34,874 --> 00:55:36,456
- Ford?
- Marvin.

761
00:55:36,584 --> 00:55:38,962
I've been talking
to the ship's computer.

762
00:55:39,087 --> 00:55:40,748
And?

763
00:55:40,839 --> 00:55:42,375
It hates me.

764
00:55:42,757 --> 00:55:45,670
No. Eddie, computer,

765
00:55:45,760 --> 00:55:49,253
is there another way
to follow the ships?

766
00:55:49,389 --> 00:55:53,849
<i>Activating Emergency Escape Pod.
It's super-neat and fun to fly.</i>

767
00:55:56,271 --> 00:55:57,761
Unbelievable.

768
00:55:57,814 --> 00:56:02,183
I'm in. OK,
Ford, do you have any idea?

769
00:56:02,318 --> 00:56:04,525
- We'll press this button.
- No.

770
00:56:06,197 --> 00:56:09,155
- This button.
- OK. Nothing's... OK.

771
00:56:09,284 --> 00:56:12,242
Good man.

772
00:56:12,287 --> 00:56:15,951
- OK, we're wobbling...
- You forgot your towel.

773
00:56:15,999 --> 00:56:18,491
Get him off me. I'll kill him.

774
00:56:18,626 --> 00:56:21,118
- OK, Ford, there's a...
- Is that better?

775
00:56:21,254 --> 00:56:23,211
No, that's worse.

776
00:56:23,298 --> 00:56:26,632
- Do what... I don't need that.
- OK.

777
00:56:26,760 --> 00:56:29,468
Stop the rocking.
Marvin, any ideas?

778
00:56:29,512 --> 00:56:33,130
I have a million ideas.
They all point to certain death.

779
00:56:33,266 --> 00:56:34,631
Thanks, Marv.

780
00:57:20,730 --> 00:57:24,815
- Magrathea.
- No, we're on the Vogon planet.

781
00:57:24,859 --> 00:57:27,521
- Yes, it is. It's Magrathea.
- This is Vogsphere.

782
00:57:27,570 --> 00:57:30,733
- Yeah, Magrathea. I know it.
- No, it's not.

783
00:57:30,865 --> 00:57:34,358
- There is no Magrathea.
- Yes, it is.

784
00:57:35,537 --> 00:57:37,699
- What are you doing?
- They took my head.

785
00:57:37,789 --> 00:57:40,622
They have these
on Arcturan megafreighters.

786
00:57:40,708 --> 00:57:43,200
They use them
when they need to concentrate.

787
00:57:43,336 --> 00:57:45,577
- What is it?
- It's a thinking cap.

788
00:57:50,301 --> 00:57:52,463
There you go.

789
00:57:56,516 --> 00:58:00,259
That should give him some zest
for about ten minutes or so.

790
00:58:00,353 --> 00:58:03,766
Now I'm feeling much better
about our predicament.

791
00:58:25,128 --> 00:58:29,247
I checked the Guide for how
to rescue a prisoner from Vogsphere.

792
00:58:29,340 --> 00:58:32,549
It said don't.
I'm assuming you have a better plan.

793
00:58:32,594 --> 00:58:35,131
Well, I kind of had this idea
that we could...

794
00:58:37,182 --> 00:58:39,423
- Did anyone see that?
- See what?

795
00:58:39,559 --> 00:58:41,425
What was it?

796
00:58:41,561 --> 00:58:45,850
Nothing, it's nothing.
It's just my imagination.

797
00:58:45,940 --> 00:58:50,229
OK, right. Now, everyone just stop
a minute, please, and look at me.

798
00:58:50,278 --> 00:58:55,193
There's definitely something
going on here.

799
00:58:57,118 --> 00:58:59,200
Just watch.

800
00:58:59,287 --> 00:59:01,278
Just watch.

801
00:59:04,667 --> 00:59:07,125
OK, I think we...

802
00:59:08,504 --> 00:59:09,960
You too.

803
00:59:11,049 --> 00:59:13,381
Yeah, what was that?

804
00:59:16,804 --> 00:59:18,795
Zaphod, what do you think?

805
00:59:22,101 --> 00:59:25,935
I think... Zarquon.
What was that?

806
00:59:26,898 --> 00:59:30,516
I'd make a suggestion,
but you wouldn't listen.

807
00:59:30,652 --> 00:59:33,519
- No one ever does.
- I have an idea.

808
00:59:33,655 --> 00:59:36,773
Ford. Kill it. Get rid of it.

809
00:59:45,166 --> 00:59:47,999
OK, don't think.

810
00:59:48,086 --> 00:59:50,578
Nobody think. No ideas.

811
00:59:50,672 --> 00:59:52,834
No theories. No nothing.

812
00:59:59,013 --> 01:00:01,630
This is crazy.
Trillian is in there somewhere.

813
01:00:01,724 --> 01:00:06,560
- We need an idea to help save her.
- I have an...

814
01:00:06,646 --> 01:00:08,762
Run.

815
01:00:38,094 --> 01:00:40,210
You're supposed to stop.

816
01:00:49,480 --> 01:00:53,724
OK, so I'm not thinking.
Not thinking. No ideas coming.

817
01:00:56,571 --> 01:00:59,734
All right, this isn't an idea
that has any merit at all,

818
01:00:59,824 --> 01:01:03,738
but, Marvin, can you give me a hand?

819
01:01:06,164 --> 01:01:08,280
OK, where is she?

820
01:01:11,252 --> 01:01:14,085
Who, the director of robot arm repair?

821
01:01:15,798 --> 01:01:20,292
Tricia Yggarstuk McMillanus of Blaard?

822
01:01:20,428 --> 01:01:23,637
No, Tricia Marie McMillan of Earth.

823
01:01:23,765 --> 01:01:25,301
Oh. Right.

824
01:01:31,147 --> 01:01:34,606
Sorry, no record of Earth.

825
01:01:35,401 --> 01:01:39,190
Galactic sector
ZZ9 Plural Z Alpha?

826
01:01:39,280 --> 01:01:42,739
- Oh, yes.
- She's lying.

827
01:01:44,243 --> 01:01:47,577
She's skinny, and she's pretty,
and she's lying.

828
01:01:48,831 --> 01:01:51,448
Here we are. Earth.

829
01:01:53,461 --> 01:01:54,917
"Destroyed."

830
01:01:55,046 --> 01:01:58,459
Do you have
a second home planet?

831
01:01:58,508 --> 01:02:02,046
- Destroyed? That's impossible.
- That's what it says here.

832
01:02:02,136 --> 01:02:07,302
Says it was destroyed to make way
for a hyperspace expressway.

833
01:02:14,607 --> 01:02:17,975
Who in their right mind
gives an order to destroy a planet?

834
01:02:20,071 --> 01:02:24,065
- He said the grey building, right?
- All the buildings are grey.

835
01:02:24,158 --> 01:02:27,492
"Give me a hand." Very funny.

836
01:02:27,578 --> 01:02:31,071
How am I supposed to drive this pod
with one arm? Stupid human.

837
01:02:36,671 --> 01:02:38,662
So you need to go back
and fill that in.

838
01:02:38,756 --> 01:02:42,090
Then, make sure, when you fill in
the facilitating form...

839
01:02:42,176 --> 01:02:47,046
Leave this to me. I'm British.
I know how to queue.

840
01:02:48,683 --> 01:02:53,849
If you'd fill that form in for me,
and return it as soon as possible.

841
01:02:53,896 --> 01:02:58,265
- Writing implements to your left...
- You're president. Can you do anything?

842
01:02:58,359 --> 01:02:59,861
Presidents don't have power.

843
01:02:59,944 --> 01:03:04,359
Their job is to draw attention away
from it. No offence. You're a great guy.

844
01:03:05,324 --> 01:03:07,361
Hey, how you doin'?

845
01:03:07,452 --> 01:03:12,197
Hey, it's me, your president.
What's goin' on? Thanks for coming.

846
01:03:12,248 --> 01:03:15,081
All right. I know
that sponge. All right.

847
01:03:15,209 --> 01:03:17,541
- Next.
- President coming through.

848
01:03:17,670 --> 01:03:20,628
How you doin', Pinhead?
No, really, it's me.

849
01:03:21,507 --> 01:03:23,339
I love kabuki. Look at that.

850
01:03:23,384 --> 01:03:25,375
Out the way.

851
01:03:27,138 --> 01:03:29,425
Give us a kiss.

852
01:03:30,475 --> 01:03:33,388
Hi, I've come about
release of a prisoner.

853
01:03:33,478 --> 01:03:35,560
Prisoner release form.

854
01:03:38,941 --> 01:03:41,194
I don't believe you.

855
01:03:41,235 --> 01:03:43,226
These are the orders.

856
01:03:48,367 --> 01:03:50,324
"Love and kisses"?

857
01:03:51,120 --> 01:03:54,579
Now, according
to the Galactic Penal Code,

858
01:03:54,665 --> 01:03:59,410
the punishment for
a presidential kidnapping

859
01:03:59,462 --> 01:04:03,251
is to be fed to
the Ravenous Bugblatter Beast of Traal.

860
01:04:04,133 --> 01:04:06,090
Good day.

861
01:04:07,762 --> 01:04:12,097
Get off of me. What the hell is that?

862
01:04:13,476 --> 01:04:17,765
No, wait, wait.
There's been some kind of mistake.

863
01:04:20,233 --> 01:04:25,854
- Tick all the boxes on the right.
- Right. Got it.

864
01:04:25,947 --> 01:04:27,938
Not that one.

865
01:04:27,990 --> 01:04:32,279
<i>What to do if you find yourself
stuck with no hope of rescue.</i>

866
01:04:32,411 --> 01:04:36,780
<i>Consider how lucky you are
that life has been good to you so far.</i>

867
01:04:36,832 --> 01:04:40,291
<i>Alternatively, if life
hasn't been good to you so far,</i>

868
01:04:40,378 --> 01:04:43,496
<i>which, given your current circumstances,
seems more likely,</i>

869
01:04:43,589 --> 01:04:47,708
<i>consider how lucky you are that
it won't be troubling you much longer.</i>

870
01:04:51,138 --> 01:04:54,051
Right, there we go.

871
01:04:54,141 --> 01:04:56,553
Kidnapping the president.

872
01:04:56,644 --> 01:05:01,104
Oh, no, she's not eligible
for release at this time.

873
01:05:01,148 --> 01:05:04,311
OK. Right.
Look, this is the President.

874
01:05:04,443 --> 01:05:06,571
OK. See, there?

875
01:05:06,654 --> 01:05:10,318
He says the kidnapping business
was a horrible misunderstanding.

876
01:05:10,366 --> 01:05:11,902
Oh, yeah.

877
01:05:11,993 --> 01:05:15,702
She meant nothing by it.
He's ordering you to let her go.

878
01:05:15,830 --> 01:05:20,540
But this isn't a presidential
release of prisoner form.

879
01:05:20,668 --> 01:05:22,659
Those are blue.

880
01:05:23,963 --> 01:05:28,002
- I'll stay here.
- All right. Hold that. OK.

881
01:05:32,680 --> 01:05:35,012
Oh, he's hungry today.

882
01:05:37,643 --> 01:05:39,179
That's blue. Right.

883
01:05:41,397 --> 01:05:44,355
- I'm not a journalist.
- We're just hanging out.

884
01:05:44,442 --> 01:05:46,979
OK, this is for Tricia McMillan.

885
01:05:47,778 --> 01:05:51,146
Tricia McMillan. OK.

886
01:05:53,326 --> 01:05:57,445
Sir, it's a release form.

887
01:05:57,538 --> 01:05:58,869
Thank you.

888
01:05:58,998 --> 01:06:02,081
She's free to go.

889
01:06:02,168 --> 01:06:04,159
Release her.

890
01:06:07,048 --> 01:06:10,882
Zaphod's here.
Well, then, that's fine then.

891
01:06:10,968 --> 01:06:12,959
Let's just go and get him.

892
01:06:21,062 --> 01:06:23,724
Who are we waiting for again?

893
01:06:27,777 --> 01:06:29,768
No, I'm serious.

894
01:06:31,739 --> 01:06:34,026
Tricia.

895
01:06:37,078 --> 01:06:39,069
- Tricia.
- Trill.

896
01:06:39,747 --> 01:06:42,660
- Hey, come on.
- You idiot.

897
01:06:42,750 --> 01:06:44,741
You signed the order to destroy Earth.

898
01:06:44,835 --> 01:06:46,667
- He did?
- I did?

899
01:06:46,754 --> 01:06:51,248
Yes. "Love and kisses, Zaphod"?
You didn't even read it, did you?

900
01:06:51,300 --> 01:06:56,090
Honey, I'm president of the Galaxy.
I don't get a lot of time for reading.

901
01:06:58,224 --> 01:07:00,056
An entire planet, my home,

902
01:07:00,101 --> 01:07:03,264
destroyed because you thought
they wanted your autograph.

903
01:07:03,312 --> 01:07:06,100
- They framed me.
- Are you an idiot?

904
01:07:06,190 --> 01:07:10,104
- Trillian.
- You knew. Why didn't you tell me?

905
01:07:10,194 --> 01:07:14,279
- He threatened me.
- Get a backbone, Arthur.

906
01:07:14,365 --> 01:07:19,485
Oh, a backbone? What about coming here
to rescue you? Thank you. My idea.

907
01:07:20,746 --> 01:07:22,737
Stupid.

908
01:07:27,044 --> 01:07:29,422
- Got your arm.
- How considerate.

909
01:07:29,463 --> 01:07:33,798
Right, then, all those lucky enough
to have two arms, hold tight.

910
01:07:50,568 --> 01:07:53,651
The president tests my patience.

911
01:07:53,779 --> 01:07:58,615
This time I shall pursue him myself.
Ready my ship.

912
01:07:58,659 --> 01:08:01,617
Fantastic. At last.

913
01:08:06,876 --> 01:08:10,210
That's one hour for lunch, everybody.

914
01:08:11,046 --> 01:08:13,174
I think I'll have soup today.

915
01:08:15,259 --> 01:08:18,797
The Encyclopaedia Galactica,
<i>in its</i> chapter on <i>love,</i>

916
01:08:18,846 --> 01:08:22,305
<i>states that it is
far too complicated to define.</i>

917
01:08:22,349 --> 01:08:26,809
The Hitchhiker's Guide
to the Galaxy has <i>this</i> to say on <i>love:</i>

918
01:08:26,937 --> 01:08:29,474
<i>"Avoid, if at all possible."</i>

919
01:08:29,523 --> 01:08:32,436
<i>Unfortunately,
Arthur Dent has never read</i>

920
01:08:32,526 --> 01:08:34,984
The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy.

921
01:08:35,112 --> 01:08:39,071
- Oh, I'm so sorry.
- No, come in.

922
01:08:39,200 --> 01:08:41,441
I didn't...

923
01:08:44,371 --> 01:08:46,032
Look...

924
01:08:46,123 --> 01:08:49,036
Trillian, I just wanted to say,
you were right,

925
01:08:49,168 --> 01:08:54,709
I should've told you, and I understand
totally if you're angry with me.

926
01:08:54,757 --> 01:08:58,466
For what it's worth,
I know how you must be feeling.

927
01:09:00,221 --> 01:09:04,556
- Can you hand me a towel?
- Yeah, sure, this...

928
01:09:06,060 --> 01:09:08,051
Thank you.

